<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="196" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1309,1514]" pageId="2" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1381,1406]" pageId="2" pageNumber="196">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species was originally collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[761,824,1381,1406]" name="Chile" pageId="2" pageNumber="196">Chile</collectingCountry>
, in Chepu, 
<collectingCountry box="[950,991,1381,1406]" name="Iceland" pageId="2" pageNumber="196">Isla</collectingCountry>
de Chiloé. This material was found in a terrestrial collection by Dr. Holdgate that was donated to the British Museum, it is a small collection containing the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1876" box="[269,369,1454,1477]" class="Arachnida" family="Crotoniidae" genus="Crotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[269,369,1454,1477]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="196">Crotonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., only represented by a single individual. This specimen was cited by Wallwork as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wallwork" authorityYear="1978" class="Arachnida" family="Crotoniidae" genus="Crotonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiloensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="196">Crotonia chiloensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the description was made from this single adult, designated as 
<typeStatus box="[1018,1120,1489,1514]" pageId="2" pageNumber="196">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
